area_value: The area of the sample section.
cold_ischemia_time_value: Time interval on ice to the start of preservation protocol.
health_status: Patient's baseline physical condition prior to immediate event leading to organ/tissue acquisition. For example, if a relatively healthy patient suffers trauma, and as a result of reparative surgery, a tissue sample is collected, the subject will be deemed “relatively healthy”.   Likewise, a relatively healthy subject may have experienced trauma leading to brain death.  As a result of organ donation, a sample is collected.  In this scenario, the subject is deemed “relatively healthy.”
metadata_schema_id: The string that serves as the definitive identifier for the metadata schema version and is readily interpretable by computers for data validation and processing. Example: 22bc762a-5020-419d-b170-24253ed9e8d9
notes: Miscellaneous details about the sample, not captured in the existing metadata fields.
organ_condition: Health status of the organ at the time of sample recovery.
pathologist_report: Further details on organ level QC checks.
perfusion_solution: Type of solution that was used to perfuse the organ.
preparation_condition: The condition by which the preparation occurred, such as was the sample placed in dry ice during the preparation.
preparation_medium: The medium used during the sample preparation
preparation_protocol_doi: DOI for the protocols.io page that describes the assay or sample procurment and preparation. For example for an imaging assay, the protocol might include staining of a section through the creation of an OME-TIFF file. In this case the protocol would include any image processing steps required to create the OME-TIFF file. Example: https://dx.doi.org/10.17504/protocols.io.eq2lyno9qvx9/v1
procedure_date: Date of procedure to procure organ.
processing_time_value: How long the tissue was being handled before the initial preservation.
quality_criteria: For example, RIN: 8.7. For suspensions, measured by visual inspection prior to cell lysis or defined by known parameters such as wells with several cells or no cells. This can be captured at a high level. "OK" or "not OK", or with more specificity such as "debris", "clump", "low clump".
sample_id: Unique HuBMAP or SenNet identifier for the sample assigned by the ingest portal. Example: HBM743.CKJW.876 or SNT923.UYTE.122
section_index_number: The index number for the section if the sample is a single section.
source_id: Unique HuBMAP or SenNet identifier for the source (parent) from which the sample was taken. Example: HBM122.EFGH.789 or SNT234.RTYU.119
source_storage_duration_unit: The time duration unit of measurement
source_storage_duration_value: How long was the source material (parent) stored, prior to this sample being processed.
specimen_preservation_temperature: The temperature of the medium during the preservation process.
specimen_tumor_distance_value: If surgical sample, how far from the tumor was the sample obtained from. Typically a number of centimeters. Leave blank if not applicable or unknown.
storage_medium: What was the sample preserved in.
storage_method: The method by which the sample was stored, after preparation and before the assay was performed.
suspension_entity_count: Total number of cell/nuclei yielded post dissociation and enrichment.
suspension_entity_type: The type of single cell entity derived from isolation protocol.
tissue_weight_unit: The tissue weight unit of measurement
tissue_weight_value: The weight of a tissue block or the piece of tissue used in a suspension. Knowing the weight of the parent block and tissue used in a suspension, allows us to compute what percentage of the block was used for the suspension.
vital_state: Identify the vital state of the donor.
warm_ischemia_time_value: Time interval between cessation of blood flow and cooling to 4C.
